<b>Κalyvia</b> or <b>Kalivia</b> (Greek: Καλύβια) is a village in <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<prefecture wordnetid="108626947" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../386/18386.xml">
Laconia</link></district>
</location>
</prefecture>
</administrative_district>
</region>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../108/12108.xml">
Greece</link></country>
, located on the <link>
Bay of Skoutari</link>. It is part of the municipality <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<municipality wordnetid="108626283" confidence="0.8">
<geographical_area wordnetid="108574314" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<urban_area wordnetid="108675967" confidence="0.8">
<city wordnetid="108524735" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../608/1334608.xml">
Gytheio</link></city>
</urban_area>
</district>
</geographical_area>
</municipality>
</location>
</administrative_district>
</region>
. It is on the beach, and its economy is based on olives, olive oil and fishing. The town has a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../644/1305644.xml">
plateia</link> and a cafe. It has a  population of 50.  Kalyvia is linked by a road encircling the <land wordnetid="109334396" confidence="0.8">
<peninsula wordnetid="109388848" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../428/349428.xml">
Mani Peninsula</link></peninsula>
</land>
 from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../934/2697934.xml">
Vathia</link>.  Farmlands and forests cover the valley areas  around the village, although the greater surrounding area is hilly scrubland.
